    <article id="main-content" class="article">
      <header class="article-header">
        <h1 title="Minimum Network Requirements " class="article-title">
          Minimum Network Requirements 
          
        </h1>

      </header>

      <section class="article-info">
        <div class="article-content">
          <div class="article-body"><h2>General Bandwidth Recommandations&nbsp;</h2>
<p>We recommend to use a private network, dedicated for Dazzl and as stable as possible (without fluctuations).</p>
<p>To ensure optimal conditions, we recommend :</p>
<ul>
<li>Minimum of 2.5 Mbps (upload) per capture device for 720p and 6 Mbps (upload) for 1080p.&nbsp;</li>
<li>For the Live producer computer, a minimum of 10 Mbps (download) for the production platform and an additional 3 Mbps (download) per source added.</li>
</ul>
<p><em>For example, if three phones are used to film the event, 19 Mbps (download) will be needed for the producer's computer (10+3+3+3). And if this event is broadcasted in 720p, 3 Mbps (upload) for each phone.</em></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></div>
          
        </div>
      </section>

